Dialogue:
Fruits of the Navigator's
loins! Straight from the
depths of Her salty womb!

O Llymlaen! See me safe
to Fisherman's Bottom!
That's a fine rod. A fine rod, indeed.

That's quite the price
for a mere three bags.

That's what all my
customers tell me.

Ye'd both do better back
in the guild polishin'
yer masts! Hah hah hah!

The decks, they be
stained with the blood o'
more men than there be
in all o' Limsa.

We may be pirates,
but we ain't uncivilized.

I just catch the fish and
leave the mongerin' to her.

Greetin's, love. Aught I
can interest you in?

My loins throb like
Dalamud! My heart
burns like Megaflare!

You have such a
way with words!

The Sirens don't 'ave
time for men, unless
they's warmin' our beds.

Don't tell me you've not
heard of Thal Icebound!
You wish me to sing a song of your deeds?

Might be there is.
But it ain't fishes.

Why'd I wear
my mail for this?

I reckon one could
burn just about anything
in there.

Is them buzzards
I see a-circlin'?

Swabbin' be a rat's job,
if ye ask me.

Tell us where ye hid
the loot, ye rotten scrag!

Like if I sat on
yer back, ox-breath?

I'm looking for
the custom house.

When I said I'd follow you
to the ends of the realm,
I didn't think we'd need
to stop and ask directions.

Where in the Navigator's
name are the airships!?

I need sixteen bags
of the root by sunrise.

A damn hard place, this
Quarterstone. Damn hard.

Saws me a blue canary!
A blue canary, it was! Hic!

To be back at sea...
What I wouldn't give...

Another day older
and deeper in debt...

I've been hit harder
by an ocean breeze!

He lied there with her
in the dark,♪

And not a word
was spoke...♪

What in the Navigator's
name are we doin' here?

Wivout no ship, we's use-
less as teats on a flounder.

Why won't ye quit, ye
bloody sea cow!?

But what of
all the Qiqirn?

There be fish aplenty
off the Salt Strand.

A little more over
here, lemoncake.

The Navigator smiles
upon me today!

She's merely laughin'
at your paltry catch!

And why should I take
on a scrag as yerself?

I want to see
him fly, Captain.

Well then, milord,
what is your assessment?

I love ye! Come
and be me saltwife!

I's a...a bodice assessor
wiv Mealvaan's Gate.

I am going to need you
to sign this import slip.
Are you suggesting I accept a bribe, madam?

Five box o' sparklies...
Ten sack o' shinies...

Longstand makes gobbie-
legs shake and quake.

Keep your voice low, lest
you disturb the summons.

An undercover intelli-
gencer? It might just work.

What if we were to plant
an assessor on the ship?
Could you be any more specific, sir?

Very good! He's
located the milkroot!
Higher, ladies. Striking them there will only make your targets angrier.

Might be a couple
nights in the brig
will learn you.

And the special ingre-
dient is...love! Gah hah
hah! I always wanted
to say that.

After the Calamity... I...
I never thought I'd... \<sob>

This is where
we first met...

It seemed a fitting place
to say our farewells.

You're coming with
me to the brig!
I'd like to see ye try!

Mamool must be show-
ing the sparkly first, yes?

You'll sssee no gold
until we ssseal the
pact in blood, ratman.

But see, this slip says I
will give you the jingly-
shine when I get it.

Jus' give 'im the coin,
or we'll be here all night.

Ain't no one'll blink an
eye if you <If(IntegerParameter(4))>go an' singe
yer frillies in the forge<Else/>go an' stick yer
manhood in the forge</If>.

Let me see... There is an
opening ten summers hence.

I need a ship!
One what won't sink!

<If(IntegerParameter(4))>Ain't never seen
a man swing a sledge?<Else/>Get them winkers off me
forgemate's dugs, 'fore I
renders ye black an' blue.</If>

This is harder
than it looks.

I needs me a scrag to
do me scrag work.

Used to be we had
Qiqirn swab the decks.

All I wanted was
an eggless omelette.
Admiral's decree. You've a problem, you take it up with her.

Back to the
sea with ye, 'Cuda!

You going to let him
push you around like
that, love!?

There are oils
which can help...

Me ship needs all the
salted cod ye can spare.

There are still chores
that need attending!

And by the sounds of it,
gobs what need stuffin'!

<If(IntegerParameter(4))>Stay the seven hells
away from me boys, hear?<Else/>See aught ye like?</If>

What ye waitin' fer? An
invite from the Admiral?

Come a li'l closer, like.
I dinnae 'ear ye!

Ye fall to that scrag,
yer arse is mine!

Fiffy gil on the...on the...
on theone innnblue! Hic!

But in the morning
when he woke,♪

He saw the maiden
was a goat!♪

These'll make
a fine sour red.

And how am I to reach
those ones at the top?

The winner can
warm me bunk!

Ye goin' to let 'im
talk to ye like that?

And now he's telling
everyone he's gone
and lain with a mermaid!

You worry overmuch!
The captain is malms away.

Any longer and the
captain will report us!

The fiends will arrive
shortly. Make ready.

And remember, you're
not pirates anymore! I'll
have no corpse looting.

To ripe thy fruit
and spread thy seed,
and nourish those
that tend thee...♪

A sprinkle here...
A sprinkle there...
Another sprinkle here...

You haven't the stones
to work down there!

I hear they're looking
for men to mortar
the Embrace.

Blast! That crate was to
last us the whole moon!
This is not where that goes! Off with you now!

Where would ye have
these sacks of dodo feed?
